name: Charlotte Stokely
description:
📝Biography 📝

🌟Charlotte Stokely 🌟

A retired American model and TV actress was born as Brittney Vitale on August 8, 1986 in Salt Lake City, Utah. She first started modelling and performing at age 19. Stokely has also modelled for American Apparel and appeared in mainstream films and TV shows. She has modelled for several American Apparel advertisements, and even caught the attention of Dov Charney, the company's founder and CEO. Charney was a fan of her work and asked her to come in for some test shots. Stokely has also appeared uncredited in the 2009 comedy film Black Dynamite and starred in the 2014 TV movie Eve's Secret. She was a contestant on the reality television show Jenna's American Sex Star and has also appeared on the TV series Submission.

Stokely's career in the adult entertainment industry has not been without controversy. Despite this, Stokely has become a popular figure in the industry, earning a nomination for Best New Starlet at the AVN Awards in 2007. Stokely is 5'3" tall and has blonde hair, blue eyes, and a slim build with an incredibly rotund butt, with measurements of 34B-24-36.

💡Generation Advice💡

🔧Prompt and Sampling 🔧

  • Most images have been generated with Lora weighted between 1 - 1.25.

  • All example images have been done with CyberRealistic v1.4.

  • If doing a portrait headshot, to maintain the model's face during a hi-res fix, it is best to use 8x NMKD Faces upscaler at ~0.15 denoise strength. The higher you go the more clarity but the more prone to lose accuracy.

🚀Upscaling🚀

  • Ultimate SD upscale script used for all upscales ~.15 - .4 denoising using 8x NMKD Faces or 4X UltraSharp redraw upscalers.

  • The closer the face (or larger the image), the lower the denoise should be set to prevent "oddities".

  • Expand your tile width/height, mask blur and padding respectively the larger you scale your image.

🗒️Side Notes🗒️

  • Doing these LARAs are forcing me to get my prompt game tight. 👌😎

  • Leave a review if you liked it.

  • Leave a comment if you are having issues getting good output, I'll try to respond.
